@vrothberg absolutely!

I think we should just use Podman `pkg/rootless` to setup the user namespace.  The logic here is simpler as it needs only to access the storage, so we'll need the create the namespace in any case (`rootless.BecomeRootInUserNS()`).  When running in rootless user the storage must default to `~/local/share/containers/storage` instead of `/var/lib/containers/storage`, and `storage.conf` must be read from `~/.config/containers/storage.conf`.

There are cases where the namespace cannot be created so we would probably want to skip its creation, e.g. `skopeo --version|--help`
